{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861834742,"sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","part":{"id":"prt_d799d210f001tWMRC1xM1UMEQR","messageID":"msg_d799cf58b001qeC2ecFoCytehJ","sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9ad9c7f6186d4c0e85a4a3b116f7d228","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## 模块信息\n4: \n5: - **模块**: `pkg/store`\n6: - **语言**: Go\n7: - **规模**: S\n8: - **关联需求**: AR-014\n9: \n10: ## 架构概述\n11: \n12: ### 设计目标\n13: \n14: 为 AgentCube 会话存储提供 Valkey 后端实现，与 Redis 实现共享统一的 Store 接口，支持通过 `STORE_TYPE` 环境变量运行时选择存储后端。\n15: \n16: ### 核心组件\n17: \n18: ```\n19: pkg/store/\n20: ├── store.go              # Store 接口定义和错误类型\n21: ├── singleton.go          # 单例模式和存储提供者选择\n22: ├── store_redis.go        # Redis 实现\n23: └── store_valkey.go       # Valkey 实现（本设计重点）\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ### 架构原则\n27: \n28: 1. **接口一致性**: Valkey 实现必须完整遵循 `Store` 接口契约\n29: 2. **策略模式**: 通过 `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 环境变量激活 Valkey 实现\n30: 3. **单例访问**: 使用 `sync.Once` 确保存储实例的线程安全初始化\n31: 4. **错误语义一致性**: 与 Redis 实现保持相同的错误类型和语义\n32: \n33: ## 数据结构\n34: \n35: ### Store 接口\n36: \n37: ```go\n38: package store\n39: \n40: import (\n41:     \"context\"\n42:     \"time\"\n43: \n44:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n45: )\n46: \n47: type Store interface {\n48:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n49:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n50:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n51:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n52:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n53:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n54:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n55:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n56:     Close() error\n57: }\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ### SandboxInfo 结构体\n61: \n62: 存储的 JSON 文档反序列化到 `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type SandboxInfo struct {\n66:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n67:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n68:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n69:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n70:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n71:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n72:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n73:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n74:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n75: }\n76: \n77: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n78:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n79:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n80:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n81: }\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### 错误定义\n85: \n86: ```go\n87: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### 存储提供者类型常量\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: const (\n94:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n95:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n96: )\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ## Valkey 实现\n100: \n101: ### 数据结构\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: type valkeyStore struct {\n105:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n106:     sessionPrefix        string\n107:     expiryIndexKey       string\n108:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ### 固定键模式\n113: \n114: | 字段 | 值 |\n115: |------|-----|\n116: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n117: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n118: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n119: \n120: ### 连接选项 (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n121: \n122: ```go\n123: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n124:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n125:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: 可选配置：\n130: - `DisableCache`: 当 `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` 解析为 true 时启用（使用 `strconv.ParseBool`，必须严格为 true）\n131: - `ForceSingleClient`: 当 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` 解析为 true 时启用\n132: \n133: ### 环境变量\n134: \n135: | 变量 | 必需 | 说明 |\n136: |------|------|------|\n137: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | 是 | 逗号分隔地址列表 → `InitAddress` |\n138: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | 是（除非 `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`） | |\n139: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | 否 | `\"true\"` 启用 `DisableCache` |\n140: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 否 | `\"true\"` 启用 `ForceSingleClient` |\n141: | `STORE_TYPE` | 必须 | 大小写不敏感，必须为 `valkey` |\n142: \n143: ### 操作实现细节\n144: \n145: | 方法 | Valkey API |\n146: |------|-----------|\n147: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n148: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n149: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n150: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; 成功要求 `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n151: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n152: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n153: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | 同上，作用于 `last_activity` key |\n154: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 必须为 1; 然后 `Zadd` |\n155: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n156: \n157: ### ZSET 分数语义\n158: \n159: - **过期索引**: 分数 = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())`（存储时）\n160: - **最后活动**: 分数 = `float64(time.Now().Unix())`（`StoreSandbox` 时）；`float64(at.Unix())`（`UpdateSessionLastActivity` 时）\n161: \n162: ### MGET 注意事项（Valkey）\n163: \n164: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 构建所有 `session:{id}` 键并使用单个 `Mget`\n165: - 注释要求键必须在同一槽位（部署考虑）\n166: \n167: ## 单例模式\n168: \n169: ### 实现\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: var (\n173:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n174:     provider      Store\n175: )\n176: \n177: func Storage() Store\n178: func initStore() error\n179: ```\n180: \n181: - `Storage()` 调用 `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`；失败时 `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`\n182: \n183: ## API 契约\n184: \n185: ### 错误处理\n186: \n187: 1. **未找到错误**: 所有查询操作在键不存在时返回 `ErrNotFound`\n188: 2. **空值检查**: `StoreSandbox` 拒绝 nil 沙箱或零值 `ExpiresAt`\n189: 3. **幂等性保证**: `StoreSandbox` 使用 `SETNX` 确保键不存在时才创建\n190: 4. **原子性**: 批量操作使用 `DoMulti`，任一命令失败则整体失败\n191: \n192: ### 键命名规范\n193: \n194: - 主键格式: `session:{sessionID}`\n195: - 过期索引: `session:expiry`（ZSET，成员=sessionID，分数=ExpiresAt）\n196: - 最后活动索引: `session:last_activity`（ZSET，成员=sessionID，分数=最后活动时间）\n197: \n198: ### 索引使用场景\n199: \n200: | 索引 | 用途 | 查询模式 |\n201: |------|------|---------|\n202: | `session:expiry` | 垃圾回收：已过期会话 | `ZRANGEBYSCORE -inf {now}` |\n203: | `session:last_activity` | 垃圾回收：长期不活跃会话 | `ZRANGEBYSCORE -inf {inactiveThreshold}` |\n204: \n205: ### Valkey 特定行为\n206: \n207: 1. **Nil 检测**: 使用 `IsValkeyNil()` 函数检测空响应\n208: 2. **错误处理**: 检查 `ToString() == \"OK\"` 确认操作成功\n209: 3. **批量加载**: 使用 `Mget` 批量获取会话数据\n210: \n211: ## 测试策略\n212: \n213: ### 单元测试\n214: \n215: - **接口契约测试**: 使用 Valkey client mock 验证所有方法的输入输出契约\n216: - **错误路径测试**: 验证 `ErrNotFound` 的各种触发场景（键不存在、ValkeyNil 等）\n217: - **边界条件**: 空 sessionID、零时间、负 limit 等\n218: - **并发安全**: 验证 `sync.Once` 在多 goroutine 调用时的行为\n219: \n220: ### 集成测试\n221: \n222: - **Valkey 集成**: 使用真实 Valkey 实例\n223: - **端到端测试**: 完整的生命周期流程（创建、更新、查询、删除）\n224: - **索引验证**: 验证 ZSET 与主键的一致性\n225: - **MGET 测试**: 验证批量加载的正确性和性能\n226: \n227: ### 性能测试\n228: \n229: - **批量查询**: `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` 的性能\n230: - **并发写入**: 验证 `DoMulti` 的并发安全性\n231: - **内存使用**: 监控连接池和内存分配\n232: \n233: ## 依赖项\n234: \n235: | 依赖 | 版本 | 用途 |\n236: |------|------|------|\n237: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis 客户端（Redis 实现） |\n238: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.x | Valkey 客户端（本实现核心） |\n239: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | 日志记录（Valkey 选项日志） |\n240: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | - | SandboxInfo 类型定义 |\n241: \n242: ## 部署考虑\n243: \n244: ### Valkey 集群\n245: \n246: - **MGET 约束**: `MGET` 操作要求所有键在同一槽位\n247: - **单节点模式**: 使用 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` 可在单节点部署\n248: - **缓存控制**: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` 可禁用客户端缓存以获得强一致性\n249: \n250: ### 监控指标\n251: \n252: - **连接池状态**: 活跃连接、空闲连接、等待连接数\n253: - **操作延迟**: P1/P99 延迟\n254: - **错误率**: 连接失败、命令失败、未找到率\n255: - **存储大小**: 会话数量、内存占用\n256: \n257: ## 扩展性考虑\n258: \n259: ### 未来存储后端\n260: \n261: 1. **接口扩展**: 通过嵌入 `Store` 接口添加新方法\n262: 2. **向后兼容**: 确保新后端实现完整接口契约\n263: 3. **配置扩展**: 添加新的 `STORE_TYPE` 值和对应的初始化逻辑\n264: \n265: ### 性能优化\n266: \n267: 1. **批量操作**: 添加批量存储/更新方法\n268: 2. **缓存层**: 在应用层添加 LRU 缓存\n269: 3. **异步写入**: 非关键路径使用异步写入提升吞吐\n270: \n271: ## 安全考虑\n272: \n273: ### 连接安全\n274: \n275: - 强制要求密码认证（除非明确禁用）\n276: - 使用 TLS 连接加密传输\n277: - 定期轮换密码\n278: \n279: ### 数据安全\n280: \n281: - 敏感字段（如密码）不应存储在会话元数据中\n282: - 实施访问控制和审计日志\n283: - 定期备份和恢复测试\n284: \n285: ## 故障处理\n286: \n287: ### 连接故障\n288: \n289: - 自动重连机制\n290: - 退避策略（指数退避）\n291: - 熔断器模式防止级联故障\n292: \n293: ### 数据一致性\n294: \n295: - `DoMulti` 原子性保证\n296: - 最终一致性容忍（如索引与主键短暂不一致）\n297: - 修复脚本处理孤儿键（ZSET 成员但主键缺失）\n298: \n299: ## 与 Redis 实现的对比\n300: \n301: | 特性 | Redis | Valkey |\n302: |------|-------|--------|\n303: | 客户端库 | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` |\n304: | 连接选项 | `*redisv9.Options` | `*valkey.ClientOption` |\n305: | Nil 检测 | `redis.Nil` 错误 | `IsValkeyNil()` 函数 |\n306: | 批量操作 | `Pipeline()` | `DoMulti()` |\n307: | 命令构建 | 客户端方法 | Builder 模式 (`B()`) |\n308: | 地址配置 | 单地址 | 逗号分隔地址列表 |\n309: | 客户端缓存 | 不支持 | `DisableCache` 选项 |\n310: | 单客户端模式 | 不支持 | `ForceSingleClient` 选项 |\n\n(End of file - total 310 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n## 模块信息\n\n- **模块**: `pkg/store`\n- **语言**: Go\n- **规模**: S\n- **关联需求**: AR-014\n\n## 架构概述\n\n### 设计目标\n\n为 AgentCube 会话存储提供 Valkey 后端实现，与 Redis 实现共享统一的 Store 接口，支持通过 `STORE_TYPE` 环境变量运行时选择存储后端。\n\n### 核心组件\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go              # Store 接口定义和错误类型","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/store/design.md","time":{"start":1775861834718,"end":1775861834739}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861834748,"sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","part":{"id":"prt_d799d1e75001Bw3jG2TVU8myCM","messageID":"msg_d799cf58b001qeC2ecFoCytehJ","sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8d5393d39bd04cd19a19b00433e69c3a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package controller\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"math/rand\"\n7: \t\"time\"\n8: \n9: \t\"github.com/google/uuid\"\n10: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n11: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n12: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n13: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n14: \n15: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/constants\"\n16: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n17: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n18: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/api\"\n19: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/client\"\n20: )\n21: \n22: type Controller interface {\n23: \tCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n24: \tCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n25: \tGetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.GetSessionResponse, error)\n26: \tDeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.DeleteSessionResponse, error)\n27: }\n28: \n29: type SandboxController struct {\n30: \tk8sClient client.Client\n31: \tstore     store.Store\n32: }\n33: \n34: func NewSandboxController(k8sClient client.Client, store store.Store) *SandboxController {\n35: \treturn &SandboxController{\n36: \t\tk8sClient: k8sClient,\n37: \t\tstore:     store,\n38: \t}\n39: }\n40: \n41: func (sc *SandboxController) CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error) {\n42: \tagentRuntime, err := sc.k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n43: \tif err != nil {\n44: \t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n45: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"AgentRuntime %s/%s not found\", req.Namespace, req.Name)\n46: \t\t}\n47: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n48: \t}\n49: \n50: \tspec, found, err := unstructured.NestedMap(agentRuntime.Object, \"spec\")\n51: \tif err != nil {\n52: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get spec: %w\", err)\n53: \t}\n54: \tif !found {\n55: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"spec not found\")\n56: \t}\n57: \n58: \tsessionID := uuid.New().String()\n59: \tsandboxName := generateSandboxName(req.Name)\n60: \n61: \tsandboxCR, err := sc.buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR(agentRuntime, sessionID, sandboxName, req.Name, req.Namespace)\n62: \tif err != nil {\n63: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox CR: %w\", err)\n64: \t}\n65: \n66: \tsandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n67: \t\tSessionID:    sessionID,\n68: \t\tSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n69: \t\tWorkloadName: req.Name,\n70: \t\tNamespace:    req.Namespace,\n71: \t\tKind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n72: \t\tStatus:       \"pending\",\n73: \t\tCreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n74: \t\tExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n75: \t}\n76: \n77: \tif err := sc.store.StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n78: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to store sandbox: %w\", err)\n79: \t}\n80: \n81: \tcreatedCR, err := sc.k8sClient.CreateSandbox(ctx, req.Namespace, sandboxCR)\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\tsc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n84: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n85: \t}\n86: \n87: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)\n88: \tdefer cancel()\n89: \n90: \tvar podIP string\n91: \tfor i := 0; i < 60; i++ {\n92: \t\tpodIP, err = sc.k8sClient.GetPodIP(ctx, sandboxName, req.Namespace, createdCR)\n93: \t\tif err == nil {\n94: \t\t\tbreak\n95: \t\t}\n96: \t\tselect {\n97: \t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n98: \t\t\tsc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n99: \t\t\tsc.k8sClient.DeleteSandbox(ctx, req.Namespace, sandboxName)\n100: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox creation timed out\")\n101: \t\tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Second):\n102: \t\t\tcontinue\n103: \t\t}\n104: \t}\n105: \n106: \tports, _, err := unstructured.NestedSlice(spec, \"ports\")\n107: \tif err != nil {\n108: \t\tsc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n109: \t\tsc.k8sClient.DeleteSandbox(ctx, req.Namespace, sandboxName)\n110: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get ports: %w\", err)\n111: \t}\n112: \n113: \tentryPoints := sc.buildEntryPoints(podIP, ports)\n114: \n115: \tsandboxInfo.SandboxID = string(createdCR.GetUID())\n116: \tsandboxInfo.PodIP = podIP\n117: \tsandboxInfo.EntryPoints = convertEntryPoints(entryPoints)\n118: \tsandboxInfo.Status = \"running\"\n119: \n120: \tif err := sc.store.UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n121: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update sandbox: %w\", err)\n122: \t}\n123: \n124: \treturn &api.CreateSandboxResponse{\n125: \t\tSessionID:   sessionID,\n126: \t\tSandboxID:   sandboxInfo.SandboxID,\n127: \t\tSandboxName: sandboxName,\n128: \t\tEntryPoints: entryPoints,\n129: \t\tCreatedAt:   sandboxInfo.CreatedAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n130: \t\tExpiresAt:   sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n131: \t}, nil\n132: }\n133: \n134: func (sc *SandboxController) CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error) {\n135: \tcodeInterpreter, err := sc.k8sClient.GetCodeInterpreter(ctx, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n136: \tif err != nil {\n137: \t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n138: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"CodeInterpreter %s/%s not found\", req.Namespace, req.Name)\n139: \t\t}\n140: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get CodeInterpreter: %w\", err)\n141: \t}\n142: \n143: \tspec, found, err := unstructured.NestedMap(codeInterpreter.Object, \"spec\")\n144: \tif err != nil {\n145: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get spec: %w\", err)\n146: \t}\n147: \tif !found {\n148: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"spec not found\")\n149: \t}\n150: \n151: \tsessionID := uuid.New().String()\n152: \tsandboxName := generateSandboxName(req.Name)\n153: \n154: \tports, _, _ := unstructured.NestedSlice(spec, \"ports\")\n155: \tif len(ports) == 0 {\n156: \t\tports = []interface{}{\n157: \t\t\tmap[string]interface{}{\n158: \t\t\t\t\"port\":     int64(8080),\n159: \t\t\t\t\"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n160: \t\t\t},\n161: \t\t}\n162: \t}\n163: \n164: \tsandboxCR, err := sc.buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR(codeInterpreter, sessionID, sandboxName, req.Name, req.Namespace, ports)\n165: \tif err != nil {\n166: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox CR: %w\", err)\n167: \t}\n168: \n169: \tsandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n170: \t\tSessionID:    sessionID,\n171: \t\tSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n172: \t\tWorkloadName: req.Name,\n173: \t\tNamespace:    req.Namespace,\n174: \t\tKind:         \"CodeInterpreter\",\n175: \t\tStatus:       \"pending\",\n176: \t\tCreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n177: \t\tExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n178: \t}\n179: \n180: \tif err := sc.store.StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n181: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to store sandbox: %w\", err)\n182: \t}\n183: \n184: \tcreatedCR, err := sc.k8sClient.CreateSandbox(ctx, req.Namespace, sandboxCR)\n185: \tif err != nil {\n186: \t\tsc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n187: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n188: \t}\n189: \n190: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)\n191: \tdefer cancel()\n192: \n193: \tvar podIP string\n194: \tfor i := 0; i < 60; i++ {\n195: \t\tpodIP, err = sc.k8sClient.GetPodIP(ctx, sandboxName, req.Namespace, createdCR)\n196: \t\tif err == nil {\n197: \t\t\tbreak\n198: \t\t}\n199: \t\tselect {\n200: \t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n201: \t\t\tsc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n202: \t\t\tsc.k8sClient.DeleteSandbox(ctx, req.Namespace, sandboxName)\n203: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox creation timed out\")\n204: \t\tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Second):\n205: \t\t\tcontinue\n206: \t\t}\n207: \t}\n208: \n209: \tentryPoints := sc.buildEntryPoints(podIP, ports)\n210: \n211: \tsandboxInfo.SandboxID = string(createdCR.GetUID())\n212: \tsandboxInfo.PodIP = podIP\n213: \tsandboxInfo.EntryPoints = convertEntryPoints(entryPoints)\n214: \tsandboxInfo.Status = \"running\"\n215: \n216: \tif err := sc.store.UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n217: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update sandbox: %w\", err)\n218: \t}\n219: \n220: \treturn &api.CreateSandboxResponse{\n221: \t\tSessionID:   sessionID,\n222: \t\tSandboxID:   sandboxInfo.SandboxID,\n223: \t\tSandboxName: sandboxName,\n224: \t\tEntryPoints: entryPoints,\n225: \t\tCreatedAt:   sandboxInfo.CreatedAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n226: \t\tExpiresAt:   sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n227: \t}, nil\n228: }\n229: \n230: func (sc *SandboxController) GetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.GetSessionResponse, error) {\n231: \tsandboxInfo, err := sc.store.GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)\n232: \tif err != nil {\n233: \t\tif err == store.ErrNotFound {\n234: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"session not found\")\n235: \t\t}\n236: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get session: %w\", err)\n237: \t}\n238: \n239: \treturn &api.GetSessionResponse{\n240: \t\tSessionID:    sandboxInfo.SessionID,\n241: \t\tSandboxID:    sandboxInfo.SandboxID,\n242: \t\tSandboxName:  sandboxInfo.SandboxName,\n243: \t\tKind:         sandboxInfo.Kind,\n244: \t\tNamespace:    sandboxInfo.Namespace,\n245: \t\tName:         sandboxInfo.WorkloadName,\n246: \t\tEntryPoints:  convertToAPIEntryPoints(sandboxInfo.EntryPoints),\n247: \t\tLastActivity: sandboxInfo.LastActivityAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n248: \t\tCreatedAt:    sandboxInfo.CreatedAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n249: \t\tExpiresAt:    sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.Format(time.RFC3339),\n250: \t\tPodIP:        sandboxInfo.PodIP,\n251: \t}, nil\n252: }\n253: \n254: func (sc *SandboxController) DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.DeleteSessionResponse, error) {\n255: \tsandboxInfo, err := sc.store.GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)\n256: \tif err != nil {\n257: \t\tif err == store.ErrNotFound {\n258: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"session not found\")\n259: \t\t}\n260: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get session: %w\", err)\n261: \t}\n262: \n263: \tif err := sc.k8sClient.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sandboxInfo.Namespace, sandboxInfo.SandboxName); err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n264: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to delete sandbox: %w\", err)\n265: \t}\n266: \n267: \tif err := sc.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID); err != nil {\n268: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to delete session: %w\", err)\n269: \t}\n270: \n271: \treturn &api.DeleteSessionResponse{\n272: \t\tSessionID: sessionID,\n273: \t\tDeletedAt: time.Now().Format(time.RFC3339),\n274: \t}, nil\n275: }\n276: \n277: func (sc *SandboxController) buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR(agentRuntime *unstructured.Unstructured, sessionID, sandboxName, workloadName, namespace string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n278: \tcr := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n279: \tcr.SetAPIVersion(\"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\")\n280: \tcr.SetKind(\"Sandbox\")\n281: \tcr.SetName(sandboxName)\n282: \tcr.SetNamespace(namespace)\n283: \n284: \tcr.SetLabels(map[string]string{\n285: \t\tconstants.LabelManagedBy:    constants.LabelManagedByValue,\n286: \t\tconstants.LabelSessionID:    sessionID,\n287: \t\tconstants.LabelWorkloadName: workloadName,\n288: \t\tconstants.LabelSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n289: \t})\n290: \n291: \tcr.SetAnnotations(map[string]string{\n292: \t\tconstants.AnnotationIdleTimeout: \"15m\",\n293: \t})\n294: \n295: \tshutdownTime := time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour)\n296: \n297: \tspec := map[string]interface{}{\n298: \t\t\"replicas\": int64(1),\n299: \t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n300: \t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n301: \t\t},\n302: \t}\n303: \n304: \tspecMap, found, err := unstructured.NestedMap(agentRuntime.Object, \"spec\", \"podTemplate\")\n305: \tif err != nil {\n306: \t\treturn nil, err\n307: \t}\n308: \tif found {\n309: \t\tspec[\"podTemplate\"] = specMap\n310: \t}\n311: \n312: \tports, _, _ := unstructured.NestedSlice(agentRuntime.Object, \"spec\", \"ports\")\n313: \tif len(ports) > 0 {\n314: \t\tspec[\"ports\"] = ports\n315: \t}\n316: \n317: \tcr.Object[\"spec\"] = spec\n318: \n319: \treturn cr, nil\n320: }\n321: \n322: func (sc *SandboxController) buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR(codeInterpreter *unstructured.Unstructured, sessionID, sandboxName, workloadName, namespace string, ports []interface{}) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n323: \tcr := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n324: \tcr.SetAPIVersion(\"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\")\n325: \tcr.SetKind(\"Sandbox\")\n326: \tcr.SetName(sandboxName)\n327: \tcr.SetNamespace(namespace)\n328: \n329: \tcr.SetLabels(map[string]string{\n330: \t\tconstants.LabelManagedBy:    constants.LabelManagedByValue,\n331: \t\tconstants.LabelSessionID:    sessionID,\n332: \t\tconstants.LabelWorkloadName: workloadName,\n333: \t\tconstants.LabelSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n334: \t})\n335: \n336: \tcr.SetAnnotations(map[string]string{\n337: \t\tconstants.AnnotationIdleTimeout: \"15m\",\n338: \t})\n339: \n340: \tshutdownTime := time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour)\n341: \n342: \tspec := map[string]interface{}{\n343: \t\t\"replicas\": int64(1),\n344: \t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n345: \t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n346: \t\t},\n347: \t}\n348: \n349: \tif len(ports) > 0 {\n350: \t\tspec[\"ports\"] = ports\n351: \t}\n352: \n353: \timage, _, _ := unstructured.NestedString(codeInterpreter.Object, \"spec\", \"template\", \"image\")\n354: \tif image == \"\" {\n355: \t\timage = \"python:3.11-slim\"\n356: \t}\n357: \n358: \tcontainer := corev1.Container{\n359: \t\tName:  \"code-interpreter\",\n360: \t\tImage: image,\n361: \t}\n362: \n363: \tpodSpec := corev1.PodSpec{\n364: \t\tContainers: []corev1.Container{container},\n365: \t}\n366: \n367: \tpodSpecMap, err := runtime.DefaultUnstructuredConverter.ToUnstructured(&podSpec)\n368: \tif err != nil {\n369: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to convert pod spec: %w\", err)\n370: \t}\n371: \n372: \tspec[\"podTemplate\"] = podSpecMap\n373: \n374: \tcr.Object[\"spec\"] = spec\n375: \n376: \treturn cr, nil\n377: }\n378: \n379: func (sc *SandboxController) buildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []interface{}) []api.EntryPoint {\n380: \tvar entryPoints []api.EntryPoint\n381: \tfor _, p := range ports {\n382: \t\tportMap, ok := p.(map[string]interface{})\n383: \t\tif !ok {\n384: \t\t\tcontinue\n385: \t\t}\n386: \n387: \t\tprotocol, _, _ := unstructured.NestedString(portMap, \"protocol\")\n388: \t\tport, _, _ := unstructured.NestedInt64(portMap, \"port\")\n389: \t\tpath, _, _ := unstructured.NestedString(portMap, \"pathPrefix\")\n390: \n391: \t\tif port == 0 || protocol == \"\" {\n392: \t\t\tcontinue\n393: \t\t}\n394: \n395: \t\tentryPoints = append(entryPoints, api.EntryPoint{\n396: \t\t\tProtocol: protocol,\n397: \t\t\tEndpoint: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", podIP, port),\n398: \t\t\tPath:     path,\n399: \t\t\tPort:     int32(port),\n400: \t\t})\n401: \t}\n402: \treturn entryPoints\n403: }\n404: \n405: func convertEntryPoints(entryPoints []api.EntryPoint) []types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n406: \tvar result []types.SandboxEntryPoint\n407: \tfor _, ep := range entryPoints {\n408: \t\tresult = append(result, types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n409: \t\t\tProtocol: ep.Protocol,\n410: \t\t\tEndpoint: ep.Endpoint,\n411: \t\t\tPath:     ep.Path,\n412: \t\t})\n413: \t}\n414: \treturn result\n415: }\n416: \n417: func convertToAPIEntryPoints(entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint) []api.EntryPoint {\n418: \tvar result []api.EntryPoint\n419: \tfor _, ep := range entryPoints {\n420: \t\tresult = append(result, api.EntryPoint{\n421: \t\t\tProtocol: ep.Protocol,\n422: \t\t\tEndpoint: ep.Endpoint,\n423: \t\t\tPath:     ep.Path,\n424: \t\t})\n425: \t}\n426: \treturn result\n427: }\n428: \n429: func generateSandboxName(workloadName string) string {\n430: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", workloadName, RandString(8))\n431: }\n432: \n433: func RandString(n int) string {\n434: \tconst charset = \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789\"\n435: \tb := make([]byte, n)\n436: \tfor i := range b {\n437: \t\tb[i] = charset[rand.Intn(len(charset))]\n438: \t}\n439: \treturn string(b)\n440: }\n\n(End of file - total 440 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package controller\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"math/rand\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/google/uuid\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/constants\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/api\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/client\"\n)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go","time":{"start":1775861834715,"end":1775861834746}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861834752,"sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","part":{"id":"prt_d799d23c00014QKmOjDF8eYD6C","messageID":"msg_d799cf58b001qeC2ecFoCytehJ","sessionID":"ses_28663384efferv1Xjt01zePk3j","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0b9530312d6d48aaa19fc82965a814e1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // +genclient\n9: // +genclient:nonNamespaced\n10: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n11: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n12: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar;agentruntime\n13: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n14: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n15: \n16: // AgentRuntime defines a custom resource for managing agent runtime configurations.\n17: // It represents a sandbox orchestration runtime that manages the lifecycle of agent pods.\n18: type AgentRuntime struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n23: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime.\n27: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n28: \t// PodTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n29: \t// +required\n30: \tPodTemplate *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n31: \n32: \t// SessionTimeout defines the timeout for idle sessions before cleanup.\n33: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n35: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n36: \t// +optional\n37: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n38: \n39: \t// MaxSessionDuration defines the maximum allowed duration for a session.\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n41: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n42: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n43: \t// +optional\n44: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: // SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n48: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n49: \t// Metadata defines labels and annotations for the pod.\n50: \t// +optional\n51: \tMetadata *SandboxMetadata `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n52: \n53: \t// Spec defines the pod specification.\n54: \tSpec SandboxPodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n55: }\n56: \n57: // SandboxMetadata defines metadata for sandbox pods.\n58: type SandboxMetadata struct {\n59: \t// Labels are key-value pairs attached to the pod.\n60: \t// +optional\n61: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n62: \n63: \t// Annotations are unstructured key-value pairs stored with the pod.\n64: \t// +optional\n65: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: // SandboxPodSpec defines the specification for sandbox pods.\n69: type SandboxPodSpec struct {\n70: \t// Containers represents the list of containers in the pod.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n72: \tContainers []SandboxContainer `json:\"containers\"`\n73: \n74: \t// NodeSelector specifies node selection constraints.\n75: \t// +optional\n76: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n77: \n78: \t// Affinity defines pod scheduling constraints.\n79: \t// +optional\n80: \tAffinity *SandboxAffinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n81: \n82: \t// Tolerations defines pod tolerations.\n83: \t// +optional\n84: \tTolerations []SandboxToleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n85: \n86: \t// ResourceRequirements defines resource requirements for the pod.\n87: \t// +optional\n88: \tResourceRequirements *SandboxResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n89: \n90: \t// Volumes defines pod volumes.\n91: \t// +optional\n92: \tVolumes []SandboxVolume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: // SandboxContainer defines a container in a sandbox pod.\n96: type SandboxContainer struct {\n97: \t// Name is the name of the container.\n98: \t// +required\n99: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n100: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n101: \n102: \t// Image is the container image.\n103: \t// +required\n104: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n105: \n106: \t// Command specifies the entrypoint array for the container.\n107: \t// +optional\n108: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n109: \n110: \t// Args specifies the arguments to the entrypoint.\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory.\n115: \t// +optional\n116: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n117: \n118: \t// Ports represents the network ports exposed by the container.\n119: \t// +optional\n120: \tPorts []SandboxContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n121: \n122: \t// Env represents environment variables.\n123: \t// +optional\n124: \tEnv []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// Resources defines compute resource requirements.\n127: \t// +optional\n128: \tResources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// VolumeMounts specifies volume mounts.\n131: \t// +optional\n132: \tVolumeMounts []SandboxVolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n133: \n134: \t// LivenessProbe defines the liveness probe.\n135: \t// +optional\n136: \tLivenessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n137: \n138: \t// ReadinessProbe defines the readiness probe.\n139: \t// +optional\n140: \tReadinessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n141: \n142: \t// SecurityContext defines security settings.\n143: \t// +optional\n144: \tSecurityContext *SandboxSecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n145: }\n146: \n147: // SandboxContainerPort defines a network port in a container.\n148: type SandboxContainerPort struct {\n149: \t// Name is the name of the port.\n150: \t// +optional\n151: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n152: \n153: \t// ContainerPort is the port number on the container.\n154: \t// +required\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n156: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n157: \tContainerPort int32 `json:\"containerPort\"`\n158: \n159: \t// Protocol is the protocol for the port.\n160: \t// +optional\n161: \t// +kubebuilder:default=TCP\n162: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n163: \n164: \t// HostPort is the port number on the host.\n165: \t// +optional\n166: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n167: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n168: \tHostPort int32 `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n169: }\n170: \n171: // SandboxEnvVar defines an environment variable.\n172: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n173: \t// Name is the name of the environment variable.\n174: \t// +required\n175: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n176: \n177: \t// Value is the literal value of the environment variable.\n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tValue string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// ValueFrom specifies a source for the value.\n182: \t// +optional\n183: \tValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n184: }\n185: \n186: // SandboxEnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable values.\n187: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n188: \t// FieldRef selects a field from the pod.\n189: \t// +optional\n190: \tFieldRef *SandboxFieldRef `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// ConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n193: \t// +optional\n194: \tConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// SecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n197: \t// +optional\n198: \tSecretKeyRef *SandboxSecretKeyRef `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: // SandboxFieldRef selects a field from a pod.\n202: type SandboxFieldRef struct {\n203: \t// FieldPath is the path of the field.\n204: \t// +required\n205: \tFieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n206: }\n207: \n208: // SandboxConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n209: type SandboxConfigMapKeyRef struct {\n210: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n211: \t// +required\n212: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n213: \n214: \t// Key is the key to select.\n215: \t// +required\n216: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n217: \n218: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n219: \t// +optional\n220: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n221: }\n222: \n223: // SandboxSecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n224: type SandboxSecretKeyRef struct {\n225: \t// Name is the name of the Secret.\n226: \t// +required\n227: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n228: \n229: \t// Key is the key to select.\n230: \t// +required\n231: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n232: \n233: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n234: \t// +optional\n235: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: // SandboxContainerResources defines resource requirements for a container.\n239: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n240: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n241: \t// +optional\n242: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n243: \n244: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n245: \t// +optional\n246: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n247: }\n248: \n249: // SandboxResourceList defines a list of resources.\n250: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n251: \t// CPU defines CPU resources.\n252: \t// +optional\n253: \tCPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n254: \n255: \t// Me